    "body": "## Purpose\n\nThe fix in https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/19648 was disruptive for Blackwell's `cutlass_moe_fp4` usage. This is because `get_cutlass_moe_mm_data` is used for both [`run_cutlass_moe_fp8` (sm90)](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/8359f4c8d840d409fe698d9bf428ecd2f7e85b75/vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/cutlass_moe.py#L146) and [`cutlass_moe_fp4` (sm100)](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/blob/8359f4c8d840d409fe698d9bf428ecd2f7e85b75/vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/cutlass_moe.py#L446)\n\nWhile trying to run the kernel, we see the following error:\n```\nNotImplementedError: No compiled get_cutlass_moe_mm_data: no cutlass_scaled_mm kernel for CUDA device capability: 100. Required capability: 90\n```\n\nThanks to @dsikka and @pavanimajety for finding this issue\n\n## Test Plan\n\nRun test on B200\n```\npytest tests/kernels/moe/test_nvfp4_moe.py\n```\n\n## Test Result\n\nBefore:\n```\n...\nFAILED tests/kernels/moe/test_nvfp4_moe.py::test_cutlass_fp4_moe_no_graph[dtype1-8-256-224-1024-1536] - NotImplementedError: No compiled get_cutlass_moe_mm_data: no cutlass_scaled_mm kernel for CUDA device capability: 100. Required capability: 90\n==== 180 failed in 68.79s (0:01:08) ====\n```\n\nAfter:\n```\n==== 180 passed in 75.16s (0:01:15) ====\n```",
    "created_at": "2025-06-25T17:41:09Z",
